WEBVTT

00:01.235 --> 00:04.669
Judge dewey, your openly
transphobic behaviour

00:04.705 --> 00:06.371
Is disgusting.

00:06.374 --> 00:08.540
I hope to never see you
in my courtroom again.

00:08.542 --> 00:09.641
Colleen:
<i> After what I just told you,</i>

00:09.776 --> 00:11.943
Do you think judge dewey
deserves to be on the bench?

00:11.979 --> 00:15.180
Judge dewey is accusing me
of professional misconduct.

00:15.249 --> 00:16.749
Stay the hell away
from my nephew. No!

00:16.884 --> 00:19.518
Colleen:
<i> I'm troubled to learn of the</i>
<i> government's callous disregard</i>

00:19.653 --> 00:21.119
For your niece's
rights as a mother.

00:21.254 --> 00:23.188
<i> Therefore, I find</i>
<i> ronnie maloney not guilty</i>

00:23.190 --> 00:24.122
On the charge of kidnapping.

00:24.191 --> 00:25.290
Trudy:
<i> Basil's gone.</i>

00:25.359 --> 00:26.858
We were supposed
to meet yesterday

00:26.894 --> 00:28.594
But he...He never showed.

00:28.729 --> 00:30.028
Ellery:
<i> I think I found him.</i>

00:30.163 --> 00:30.996
[tense suspenseful music]

00:31.131 --> 00:32.331
Marcie:
<i> We are gonna find out</i>

00:32.466 --> 00:34.533
<i> Exactly what</i>
<i> happened to him.</i>

00:44.612 --> 00:48.413
[birds chirping]
[crows cawing]

00:48.482 --> 00:53.451
[birds chirping]

00:59.292 --> 01:04.363
[melancholy music]

01:04.365 --> 01:11.036
[tense dramatic music]

01:11.105 --> 01:12.571
Carol:
<i> We are offering no evidence</i>

01:12.640 --> 01:14.372
<i> In the criminal case</i>
<i> against the defendant,</i>

01:14.408 --> 01:15.574
<i> Sister mary grace locklin,</i>

01:15.643 --> 01:17.309
<i> For the alleged</i>
<i> abuses committed</i>

01:17.311 --> 01:18.777
<i> At the pine river</i>
<i> indian day school</i>

01:18.779 --> 01:20.679
<i> On the basis that there's</i>
<i> a lack of evidence</i>

01:20.814 --> 01:22.380
To proceed with the trial.

01:23.884 --> 01:25.850
Donald:
<i> The elders told me not to</i>
<i> expect justice anyways.</i>

01:27.288 --> 01:28.787
I don't know what
I was thinkin'.

01:28.856 --> 01:30.255
[phone ringing]

01:31.058 --> 01:32.624
Cal dismissed the charges.

01:33.794 --> 01:35.260
Time for plan b.

01:36.530 --> 01:38.530
I'm happy that the crown
saw through all those lies.

01:39.800 --> 01:43.635
I put my faith in god and
I did expect this outcome.

01:46.273 --> 01:47.406
We're gonna end it here.

01:47.541 --> 01:48.674
Thank you,
ladies and gentlemen.

01:48.809 --> 01:50.542
<i> It's been a very long week</i>
<i> for sister mary grace,</i>

01:50.611 --> 01:52.211
<i> So we're gonna</i>
<i> wrap it up here.</i>

01:52.346 --> 01:53.912
Marcie:
<i> Hang tight, folks.</i>

01:55.149 --> 01:56.949
Sister mary grace locklin.

01:57.084 --> 01:58.683
You've been served.

01:58.752 --> 02:01.219
[tense music]
[camera shutters clicking]

02:01.255 --> 02:03.255
Reporter:
<i> Mr. Dubois, will you be</i>
<i> fighting this in court?</i>

02:03.390 --> 02:04.923
Reporter 2:
<i> Sister mary grace, can you</i>
<i> tell us what this is about?</i>

02:04.959 --> 02:06.491
Dubois:
<i> Thank you, everyone.</i>
<i> Thank you.</i>

02:06.494 --> 02:07.492
<i> Please, no more questions.</i>

02:07.528 --> 02:10.562
[melancholy music]

02:11.599 --> 02:12.364
Donald:
<i> There you go, there you go!</i>

02:12.433 --> 02:14.432
Atta boy, atta boy!

02:14.468 --> 02:15.433
<i> One, two, one, two!</i>

02:15.469 --> 02:16.801
Okay, switch it up!
Switch it up!

02:16.871 --> 02:17.869
<i> Come on!</i>

02:17.872 --> 02:19.337
<i> Hurry!</i>

02:20.407 --> 02:22.241
All right, all right,
water break chair, okay?

02:22.376 --> 02:24.108
Good work, bud.
Good work, man.

02:24.145 --> 02:25.310
Nice work.

02:25.312 --> 02:27.112
Hey, [speaking in mi'kmaq]

02:27.181 --> 02:28.080
Good to see you.

02:28.215 --> 02:29.481
Good to see you, too.

02:29.483 --> 02:31.917
[speaking in mi'kmaq]

02:32.052 --> 02:33.652
You're doing some great
work with these kids.

02:33.721 --> 02:34.753
Yeah.

02:34.755 --> 02:35.787
You know, it's, uh,

02:35.856 --> 02:37.389
It's good to be using
my skills, you know,

02:37.524 --> 02:38.991
For something good.

02:39.927 --> 02:41.326
So, um, is
everything on track?

02:41.461 --> 02:43.461
Yeah, I was just
checking in.

02:43.531 --> 02:45.129
You ready?

02:45.866 --> 02:48.333
[speaking in mi'kmaq]

02:48.335 --> 02:50.735
I've been waiting for
this my whole life.

02:50.771 --> 02:53.171
Donald, if we get this right,
if we get a win,

02:53.174 --> 02:55.139
Your case could inspire
prosecutors from here

02:55.176 --> 02:56.908
And across the country
just to be brave enough

02:56.977 --> 02:59.744
To pursue criminal charges
against all of these abusers.

03:01.682 --> 03:04.282
[speaking in mi'kmaq]

03:04.318 --> 03:05.784
It's for all of us.

03:05.853 --> 03:12.758
[soft dramatic music]

03:12.893 --> 03:16.395
♪

03:16.397 --> 03:17.930
[avery sighs]

03:19.733 --> 03:21.332
Are you okay?

03:21.936 --> 03:23.401
Yeah, no.

03:24.538 --> 03:26.137
I don't know.

03:28.108 --> 03:30.541
Is it about the stuff
around your birth mother?

03:31.979 --> 03:33.544
No, it's not about that.

03:36.650 --> 03:39.718
It's just, I keep waiting for
things to get back to normal

03:39.720 --> 03:40.619
Between us, but-

03:40.754 --> 03:42.221
I know, I know, I...

03:43.591 --> 03:45.356
I've just been really wrapped
up in my own head and I...

03:47.995 --> 03:49.127
But I'm back now.

03:49.129 --> 03:50.562
Yeah, back to work.

03:51.832 --> 03:53.431
Look, I'm sorry, um...

03:54.534 --> 03:55.900
Never mind.

03:56.570 --> 03:57.669
Have a good day, okay?

03:59.006 --> 04:01.172
Let's have dinner tomorrow.

04:01.242 --> 04:04.009
<i> A nice dinner just</i>
<i> the two of us,</i>

04:04.011 --> 04:05.010
No phones.

04:05.145 --> 04:06.611
Do you even know how
to turn off your phone?

04:06.614 --> 04:08.413
[both laughing]

04:22.796 --> 04:24.262
[avery chuckles]

04:28.802 --> 04:30.201
Hey.
-<i> Hey!</i>

04:31.438 --> 04:32.437
Any news?

04:32.439 --> 04:34.772
Well, uh, they sent me
her name and address

04:34.808 --> 04:35.707
But she hasn't
reached out.

04:35.842 --> 04:36.708
Well that means

04:36.843 --> 04:37.843
She didn't sign the
declaration veto,

04:37.978 --> 04:39.310
So you're free
to contact her.

04:39.346 --> 04:41.012
Yeah, I'm just...

04:41.015 --> 04:42.781
I'm just not
so sure now.

04:42.783 --> 04:44.082
Look, I get it.

04:44.151 --> 04:46.250
You're afraid that the reality
of meeting your birth mother

04:46.287 --> 04:47.185
Won't match up

04:47.321 --> 04:49.054
To whatever you got
going on in here.

04:50.824 --> 04:52.190
My advice?

04:52.192 --> 04:53.725
Do whatever you want.

04:54.528 --> 04:56.294
Whatever's best for you.

04:56.297 --> 04:59.397
Avery, you don't owe
anyone else anything.

05:00.534 --> 05:04.602
Look, we can't always
get what we want.

05:05.939 --> 05:07.673
But figuring it out,

05:07.808 --> 05:10.842
It's a good starting
point, you know?

05:10.911 --> 05:12.610
Yeah, thanks.

05:15.516 --> 05:18.550
Hey, you'll be fine
no matter what.

05:19.820 --> 05:20.819
Got it?

05:20.821 --> 05:21.820
Yeah.

05:21.822 --> 05:22.820
Got it?

05:22.856 --> 05:23.755
Got it.

05:23.890 --> 05:24.822
Okay.

05:24.858 --> 05:26.558
[melancholy music]

05:26.693 --> 05:29.160
Doug:
<i> The first of 699 indian</i>
<i> day schools in canada</i>

05:29.229 --> 05:30.762
Opened in 1880.

05:31.598 --> 05:33.798
The last one
closing in 2009.

05:33.867 --> 05:35.800
My client,
donald christmas,

05:35.869 --> 05:38.236
Is among the estimated
200,000 victims

05:38.238 --> 05:39.838
<i> From across the country.</i>

05:39.840 --> 05:42.307
<i> He attended pine river</i>
<i> indian day school.</i>

05:42.376 --> 05:44.976
<i> The evidence will show that</i>
<i> sister mary grace locklin</i>

05:44.978 --> 05:46.511
Was vice principal
of pine river

05:46.580 --> 05:48.914
From 1977 to 1991.

05:50.384 --> 05:52.350
We will further
show that she,

05:52.386 --> 05:55.787
<i>The very person responsible for</i>
<i>the well-being of the children,</i>

05:55.856 --> 05:58.322
Initiated
student-on-student
violence

05:58.359 --> 06:02.126
That was so emotionally
and physically damaging

06:02.162 --> 06:03.261
That our
client's trauma

06:03.330 --> 06:04.996
Continued right through
his adolescence

06:05.032 --> 06:06.365
In high school.

06:06.500 --> 06:08.133
<i> Eventually led to my</i>
<i> client's incarceration</i>

06:08.268 --> 06:10.902
<i> Into a juvenile detention</i>
<i>centre for the attempted murder</i>

06:10.904 --> 06:12.937
Of an older student,
jason bear.

06:12.939 --> 06:15.040
A student that
sister mary grace

06:15.042 --> 06:17.342
Coerced into attacking
young donald christmas

06:17.411 --> 06:18.977
For years.

06:19.980 --> 06:22.147
<i> We're here today</i>
<i> to seek justice.</i>

06:22.216 --> 06:24.349
<i> We're asking the court to</i>
<i> find sister mary grace locklin</i>

06:24.418 --> 06:27.953
Guilty of incitement and
assault causing bodily harm.

06:31.392 --> 06:32.524
Dubois:
<i> Your honour.</i>

06:32.526 --> 06:34.492
My client has
been demonized

06:34.528 --> 06:36.093
Because of what's been
in the media recently

06:36.130 --> 06:37.495
Regarding this
scandalous legacy

06:37.531 --> 06:39.197
Of residential schools.

06:39.332 --> 06:43.702
<i> This frail 86-year-old woman</i>
<i>is being used as the scapegoat.</i>

06:43.704 --> 06:46.037
Why place the burden
of this atrocity

06:46.039 --> 06:47.806
On one woman's
shoulders?

06:47.808 --> 06:49.106
<i> What about the</i>
<i> administrators of the school?</i>

06:49.143 --> 06:50.909
<i> Or the indian agent</i>
<i> who was stationed</i>

06:50.911 --> 06:52.710
<i> On the</i>
<i> pine river reserve?</i>

06:53.747 --> 06:57.381
Yes, residential
schools and day schools

06:57.418 --> 06:59.417
Should never
have existed,

06:59.453 --> 07:02.187
<i> But the system is to blame.</i>

07:02.322 --> 07:05.924
<i> Sister mary grace faithfully</i>
<i> performed her duties,</i>

07:05.926 --> 07:06.992
<i> As instructed,</i>

07:07.127 --> 07:09.127
<i> For nearly thirty years.</i>

07:09.196 --> 07:11.896
There is no case here,
your honour.

07:13.300 --> 07:14.899
My client is innocent.

07:19.940 --> 07:21.439
Marcie:
<i> What is a day school?</i>

07:21.442 --> 07:24.009
They were government funded,
church-run schools

07:24.144 --> 07:26.478
Located on
first nations reserves.

07:26.480 --> 07:29.214
<i> They had the same objectives</i>
<i> as residential schools,</i>

07:29.349 --> 07:33.685
<i> To assimilate indigenous</i>
<i>children into canadian society,</i>

07:33.754 --> 07:37.455
And in most cases,
the same abuses took place.

07:37.491 --> 07:41.092
Marcie:
<i>Donald christmas was identified</i>
<i> as a level two victim.</i>

07:41.128 --> 07:43.562
<i> Can you explain to the</i>
<i> court what that means?</i>

07:43.697 --> 07:47.598
Cheyenne claire:
<i> There are five levels of</i>
<i> abuse used to categorize</i>

07:47.634 --> 07:49.834
<i> The suffering of</i>
<i> the claimants.</i>

07:49.870 --> 07:52.303
And do these include
criminal acts?

07:52.305 --> 07:53.137
Yes.

07:53.207 --> 07:55.240
Harm, assault,

07:55.309 --> 07:56.574
Assault causing
bodily harm,

07:56.643 --> 07:58.342
And sexual assault.

07:58.378 --> 08:00.979
Marcie:
<i> Does your research show</i>
<i> that these types of crimes</i>

08:01.048 --> 08:03.748
Were committed at the
pine river day school?

08:03.750 --> 08:04.950
Yes.

08:04.952 --> 08:06.017
Marcie:
<i> Thank you.</i>

08:06.086 --> 08:07.986
<i> I have no further questions,</i>
<i> your honour.</i>

08:09.490 --> 08:15.093
[light dramatic music]

08:15.162 --> 08:18.396
You transported migrant worker
basil allen out of province-

08:20.801 --> 08:23.335
That is, you moved him from
nova scotia to newfoundland.

08:23.337 --> 08:24.802
Hi!

08:28.875 --> 08:30.441
Hey, lester.

08:31.512 --> 08:33.110
Excuse me.

08:35.215 --> 08:36.347
We met in p.E.I.

08:36.383 --> 08:37.982
Where you failed to mentioned
you were a clawford.

08:38.117 --> 08:40.451
Couldn't you tell from
the family resemblance?

08:42.689 --> 08:44.489
Mr. Clawford, we'd rather
not file suit against

08:44.624 --> 08:46.223
You and your
family business.

08:46.260 --> 08:47.359
Suit for what?

08:47.361 --> 08:48.693
Ellery:
<i> Mr. Allen was on that boat</i>

08:48.729 --> 08:50.996
As part of his employment
with goldenview.

08:50.998 --> 08:52.931
<i> He was under your</i>
<i> care and supervision.</i>

08:53.000 --> 08:55.366
And at some point during
that journey he was killed.

08:55.402 --> 08:56.567
Brian:
<i> According to the police,</i>

08:56.603 --> 08:59.170
Mr. Allen was drinking on
the boat and fell overboard

08:59.306 --> 09:00.972
While alone on the deck.

09:01.008 --> 09:02.040
You can prove this?

09:02.042 --> 09:03.441
That's not our job.

09:03.577 --> 09:06.711
<i> If you have concerns about the</i>
<i>voracity of this investigation,</i>

09:06.846 --> 09:08.312
You should speak
with the police.

09:08.348 --> 09:09.413
[light dramatic music]

09:09.449 --> 09:10.915
I will.

09:11.652 --> 09:12.783
You'll be hearing from us.

09:13.453 --> 09:14.920
Looking forward to it.

09:15.055 --> 09:19.457
[light dramatic music]

09:19.526 --> 09:21.226
Iris:
<i> This whole box is from</i>
<i> the residential school</i>

09:21.361 --> 09:22.860
<i> That sister mary grace</i>
<i> taught at.</i>

09:26.199 --> 09:27.632
[doug sighs]

09:28.268 --> 09:29.667
What is it?

09:29.669 --> 09:31.069
Doug:
<i> A letter written</i>
<i> by an indian agent</i>

09:31.071 --> 09:33.004
<i> On behalf of a mother who</i>
<i> hadn't heard from her child</i>

09:33.006 --> 09:34.572
In two years.

09:40.347 --> 09:42.713
Hey, I can go through
this and organize it

09:42.749 --> 09:45.183
If you wanna check
out for the day.

09:45.185 --> 09:47.218
None of this is new to me.

09:47.254 --> 09:49.154
But it doesn't
get any easier.

09:51.825 --> 09:53.558
You know, the first time I went
to school outside of eskasoni

09:53.627 --> 09:56.160
Was in the seventh grade,

09:56.229 --> 09:58.964
They bussed a handful of
us in from the reserves.

10:00.433 --> 10:03.234
Anyway, I started talking about
residential schools in class

10:03.303 --> 10:07.038
And the teacher overheard me
and he cut me off and he said,

10:08.508 --> 10:10.976
"I know everything there is
to know about canadian history

10:11.111 --> 10:12.844
"and I've never heard that!"

10:14.982 --> 10:17.548
That grown adult man
even scowled at me.

10:20.120 --> 10:21.786
There was one other
native boy in the class

10:21.788 --> 10:23.654
And he got my attention
and whispered,

10:24.724 --> 10:25.857
"my family too."

10:25.992 --> 10:27.925
[solemn music]

10:27.961 --> 10:29.727
The rest of the kids
just stared at me.

10:31.798 --> 10:33.998
I knew right then that
something wasn't right.

10:36.637 --> 10:38.136
Iris:
<i> You never told me that.</i>

10:38.972 --> 10:40.472
<i> It must've been tough.</i>

10:41.808 --> 10:43.374
My point is that,

10:44.311 --> 10:47.745
This was being
hidden for so long.

10:47.814 --> 10:49.380
Intentionally.

10:50.817 --> 10:52.283
But we lived it.

10:52.352 --> 10:59.156
[melancholy music]

10:59.192 --> 11:00.358
Doug:
<i> Do you see this?</i>

11:00.493 --> 11:02.026
Iris:
<i> Looks like a diary.</i>

11:03.163 --> 11:05.396
It was written by someone
named sister theodore.

11:05.399 --> 11:06.530
Doug:
<i> Yeah, listen.</i>

11:06.566 --> 11:09.834
<i> "dear lord: I pray,</i>
<i> I pray, I pray.</i>

11:09.836 --> 11:13.171
"I pray for the soul
with a sinister role.

11:13.306 --> 11:14.572
"for within the
purest of doves,

11:14.641 --> 11:16.373
"lies the power to ignite
the fire of hell."

11:16.410 --> 11:19.376
Oh, gave me goosebumps.

11:21.682 --> 11:22.714
[tense dramatic music]

11:22.716 --> 11:24.315
Huh.
-What?

11:25.819 --> 11:28.052
She recorded her concerns

11:28.121 --> 11:30.455
About how the children
were being treated.

11:30.457 --> 11:32.257
[tense dramatic music]

11:32.259 --> 11:33.657
By sister mary grace.

11:33.694 --> 11:35.126
[dramatic music swells]

11:37.698 --> 11:39.197
Dr. Picard:
<i> What exactly are</i>
<i> you looking for?</i>

11:39.266 --> 11:42.166
I understand you did the autopsy
on a drowning victim last week.

11:42.202 --> 11:43.868
Basil allen.

11:43.870 --> 11:45.403
I'd like a copy of the report.

11:48.842 --> 11:52.076
<i> I can only release the</i>
<i> autopsy to next of kin</i>

11:52.079 --> 11:54.212
Without the
superintendent's approval.

11:54.214 --> 11:55.647
Your mom knows that.

11:55.782 --> 11:58.049
She said you might be willing
to let me just take a look.

11:58.051 --> 11:59.551
Mmm.

11:59.553 --> 12:02.020
You kids never wanna
do it the right way.

12:02.022 --> 12:04.555
Ellery:
<i> Well actually I do</i>
<i> represent the victim's</i>

12:04.591 --> 12:06.557
Next-of-kin in canada.

12:06.593 --> 12:07.892
His fiancee, trudy willis.

12:08.027 --> 12:09.561
Well, it says here
his next-of-kin

12:09.563 --> 12:11.096
Is his mother jean allen.

12:11.865 --> 12:13.330
In jamaica.

12:14.935 --> 12:16.367
Tell me this.

12:16.369 --> 12:19.670
Are you comfortable declaring
basil allen's death an accident

12:19.706 --> 12:21.405
Precluding any
further investigation

12:21.441 --> 12:23.575
Into the cause of death?

12:23.577 --> 12:25.109
What are you talking about?

12:25.112 --> 12:26.510
I made a full
report to the rcmp,

12:26.546 --> 12:29.313
Stating that the victim died
from a blow to the head.

12:30.917 --> 12:34.318
I don't decide who they
charge or don't charge.

12:34.354 --> 12:39.857
[tense dramatic music]

12:39.926 --> 12:41.459
I'm going for a coffee.

12:42.529 --> 12:44.095
Fill your boots.

12:44.964 --> 12:46.064
I'll be back in five minutes.

12:48.502 --> 12:50.868
Tell your mother
she owes me one.

12:50.937 --> 12:56.407
[soft dramatic music]

12:56.476 --> 12:57.809
[camera clicking]

12:57.811 --> 13:04.749
[soft dramatic music]

13:04.884 --> 13:09.086
♪

13:09.122 --> 13:10.221
Father jarrod:
<i> Did sharon let you in?</i>

13:10.356 --> 13:11.822
[iris gasps]

13:12.625 --> 13:13.958
Iris:
<i> You scared me.</i>

13:13.994 --> 13:16.294
Iris beals, father?

13:16.296 --> 13:17.228
Jarrod.

13:17.297 --> 13:18.696
How can I help you?

13:18.698 --> 13:21.933
I'm looking for a nun
named sister theodore.

13:22.068 --> 13:23.568
<i> Do you know where</i>
<i> I can find her?</i>

13:23.703 --> 13:26.504
Sister theodore sadly
passed away last year.

13:26.639 --> 13:27.905
<i> What's this in regards to?</i>

13:27.974 --> 13:30.241
I'm working a case regarding
a former day school.

13:30.376 --> 13:32.643
<i> I'm familiar with the case.</i>

13:32.712 --> 13:34.511
Uh, unfortunately,
I can't help you.

13:34.548 --> 13:36.647
Well, there must
still be some records

13:36.716 --> 13:38.716
Pertaining to
sister mary grace's time here.

13:38.852 --> 13:40.318
Father jarrod:
<i> I am sorry, no.</i>

13:40.387 --> 13:42.119
She was stationed here,

13:42.155 --> 13:43.988
But she retired to the
motherhouse in quebec

13:43.990 --> 13:45.556
Fifteen years ago.

13:46.993 --> 13:49.794
This is a staff photo from when
the school was still operating?

13:49.929 --> 13:52.196
Yes, it's from the early 80s.

13:52.265 --> 13:56.134
Um, this is sister theodore
and sister mary grace

13:56.136 --> 13:58.403
<i> And some of the other</i>
<i> day school faculty.</i>

13:58.538 --> 14:00.638
Would it be possible
for me to get a copy?

14:00.707 --> 14:02.273
No, I'm-I'm sorry.

14:03.410 --> 14:06.010
We can't have anything
to do with this case.

14:06.046 --> 14:09.280
This mission was not
responsible for the day school

14:09.415 --> 14:10.748
<i> And now we're getting</i>
<i> all the blame.</i>

14:10.750 --> 14:13.817
But ignoring the church's
role in the abuses that happened

14:13.854 --> 14:15.986
Doesn't erase history.

14:16.022 --> 14:17.889
<i> If you really wanted to</i>
<i> reconcile with this community,</i>

14:18.024 --> 14:19.156
<i> You'd help.</i>

14:19.192 --> 14:21.526
<i> Father, we found</i>
<i> sister theodore's diary</i>

14:21.528 --> 14:24.162
And she was very upset with
what happened back then.

14:24.164 --> 14:27.498
<i> If she was still alive,</i>
<i> I'm sure she'd wanna help.</i>

14:27.567 --> 14:30.168
<i> All I want is to find</i>
<i> someone, anyone,</i>

14:30.303 --> 14:31.302
Who knew her,

14:31.338 --> 14:34.372
Who could maybe
corroborate what she wrote.

14:34.374 --> 14:36.641
So that her voice
can still be heard.

14:36.710 --> 14:38.209
[light dramatic music]

14:38.278 --> 14:39.743
[father sighs]

14:41.381 --> 14:43.114
I appreciate the heads up,

14:43.116 --> 14:44.682
But just go ahead
and cooperate.

14:46.486 --> 14:47.952
I'll be fine.

14:48.087 --> 14:49.620
Don't worry.

14:50.590 --> 14:52.457
Thanks, take care.

14:52.592 --> 14:55.793
<i> That investigator from</i>
<i> the barristers' society,</i>

14:55.862 --> 14:57.528
Looks like they're calling
everyone looking for dirt.

14:57.597 --> 14:58.930
Doug:
<i> Yeah, I got the call too.</i>

14:59.065 --> 15:01.399
Just finding myself
too busy to call back.

15:01.401 --> 15:02.866
Hmm.

15:03.403 --> 15:04.402
Are you worried?

15:04.404 --> 15:05.869
Marcie:
<i> No.</i>

15:07.073 --> 15:08.506
Yes.

15:08.641 --> 15:10.474
<i> But I will deal</i>
<i> with it later.</i>

15:10.510 --> 15:14.712
We have to work on our argument
to get this into evidence.

15:14.781 --> 15:16.280
Sister theodore's diary.

15:16.283 --> 15:19.350
Aka sister mary grace's
official record of employment

15:19.386 --> 15:23.021
Issued at the pine river day
school by her supervisor,

15:23.156 --> 15:24.689
Sister theodore.

15:25.358 --> 15:27.158
Let's get to work.

15:27.160 --> 15:28.693
[suspenseful music]

15:29.663 --> 15:30.861
Martin:
<i> Thanks for seeing me.</i>

15:30.931 --> 15:33.530
<i> I wanted to talk to you</i>
<i> about the ronnie maloney case</i>

15:33.566 --> 15:35.233
That you argued last year.

15:35.235 --> 15:37.001
Right. The child
abduction case.

15:37.003 --> 15:38.836
Is this about the appeal?

15:38.838 --> 15:40.637
Opposing counsel
was doug paul.

15:41.942 --> 15:44.175
Martin, if you're concerned
about me being in conflict.

15:44.310 --> 15:45.443
Marcie diggs she
didn't approach me-

15:45.445 --> 15:48.713
It's not about you
being in conflict.

15:52.152 --> 15:53.751
What was martin jesper
doing here?

15:53.820 --> 15:55.453
<i> Did he offer you</i>
<i> your old job back?</i>

15:55.455 --> 15:57.655
He's adding grounds to
the ronnie maloney appeal,

15:57.657 --> 15:59.857
<i> Says that colleen should</i>
<i> have recused herself</i>

15:59.993 --> 16:01.993
Or that I should've asked
her to recuse herself.

16:02.062 --> 16:03.427
<i> That appeal's been</i>
<i> going on for months</i>

16:03.496 --> 16:06.530
And now they're just
noticing who the judge was?

16:06.599 --> 16:08.899
Ronnie maloney does
not deserve this.

16:08.935 --> 16:10.601
I'm just the messenger.

16:10.670 --> 16:12.904
I'll make some calls,
see what I can find out.

16:14.341 --> 16:15.740
[phone ringing]

16:20.146 --> 16:21.012
[door knocking]

16:21.081 --> 16:22.546
Ms. Beals?

16:23.216 --> 16:24.081
I'm eddie mcdonaugh,

16:24.150 --> 16:25.683
We spoke on the
phone earlier.

16:25.818 --> 16:27.351
Yes, hi!

16:27.354 --> 16:28.886
Thank you for
agreeing to meet.

16:28.955 --> 16:30.421
<i> Please.</i>

16:31.324 --> 16:34.691
I was surprised
to get your call.

16:34.728 --> 16:39.263
I found your name in a diary
written by a sister theodore?

16:39.332 --> 16:40.765
Well...

16:42.168 --> 16:43.968
Thank god you found me.

16:44.037 --> 16:45.502
What?

16:46.572 --> 16:49.574
The things that I
saw at that school.

16:49.709 --> 16:51.976
[haunting music]

16:52.111 --> 16:54.512
It's been eating me
alive for years.

16:54.581 --> 16:57.115
[haunting music continues]

16:57.117 --> 16:58.783
That's ridiculous!

16:58.852 --> 17:01.052
On what grounds could they
possibly wanna overturn

17:01.187 --> 17:02.653
My verdict on the
maloney case?

17:02.655 --> 17:04.288
They're saying since
you're boss at legal aid

17:04.290 --> 17:05.522
That you shouldn't
have heard the case.

17:05.558 --> 17:08.126
I was harder on you than
anybody else in that courtroom!

17:08.261 --> 17:09.260
<i> It doesn't matter.</i>

17:09.395 --> 17:10.862
It's perception, right?

17:13.266 --> 17:14.866
If ronnie maloney has to
go through a new trial

17:15.001 --> 17:16.067
Because of me I-

17:16.202 --> 17:18.368
Let's hope that the appeals
court refuses to hear it.

17:19.973 --> 17:21.639
Hey, listen, I gotta go.

17:21.774 --> 17:23.708
Good to see you, colleen.

17:23.710 --> 17:25.043
You're coming to
our wedding, right?

17:25.178 --> 17:28.079
Yes, sorry.
I forgot to rsvp.

17:28.214 --> 17:29.546
<i> Of course I'm coming!</i>

17:29.582 --> 17:31.348
You're my best friend,
who I automatically

17:31.384 --> 17:33.017
Let win in my courtroom,
right?

17:33.086 --> 17:34.485
[doug chuckles]

17:34.521 --> 17:35.953
See ya.

17:37.290 --> 17:40.558
We've uncovered a journal
kept by a former principal

17:40.627 --> 17:43.694
At pine river and we would
like it admitted as evidence.

17:43.829 --> 17:45.062
On what grounds?

17:45.065 --> 17:48.265
Sister theodore was
sister mary grace's supervisor.

17:48.301 --> 17:50.567
We are submitting ledgers
and employment records

17:50.603 --> 17:53.637
That correlate with the
entries written in the journal.

17:53.639 --> 17:56.273
<i> The dates also coincide</i>
<i> with the abuses</i>

17:56.309 --> 17:57.675
That sister theodore recorded

17:57.744 --> 18:00.878
And said that sister mary grace
was the perpetrator.

18:00.914 --> 18:02.646
Your honour, we've
reviewed this document.

18:02.715 --> 18:04.047
It is a diary.

18:04.084 --> 18:07.018
It's a private diary written
by a nun who is now deceased.

18:07.153 --> 18:08.786
It's impossible to
test its voracity.

18:08.855 --> 18:10.521
Marcie:
<i> It was a working journal</i>

18:10.657 --> 18:13.524
That logged all of the
official performance details

18:13.659 --> 18:14.926
From teachers and students.

18:14.928 --> 18:16.060
Now if I may,

18:16.129 --> 18:19.330
I'd like to just read a
small section to the court.

18:19.332 --> 18:23.901
<i> On October 22nd, 1982,</i>
<i> sister theodore wrote:</i>

18:25.338 --> 18:28.739
"I resuscitated a small child
from the primary class today

18:28.808 --> 18:30.475
"who's named donald christmas

18:30.610 --> 18:35.246
"after he was attacked by an
older student named jason bear.

18:35.248 --> 18:36.780
<i> "upon questioning,</i>
<i> jason said</i>

18:36.816 --> 18:39.483
"that he was instructed
by sister mary grace

18:39.486 --> 18:42.052
"to punish donald because
he had soiled himself."

18:42.088 --> 18:43.187
End quote.

18:43.189 --> 18:44.355
Objection, your honour.

18:44.490 --> 18:45.389
<i> That's hearsay.</i>

18:45.525 --> 18:46.490
It's a business record.

18:46.559 --> 18:49.060
None of that makes any
of these entries true.

18:49.195 --> 18:51.161
Your honour, the descriptive
content goes far beyond

18:51.197 --> 18:52.296
Employment records.

18:52.298 --> 18:53.997
Without the author
here to testify,

18:54.033 --> 18:55.766
I can't properly
defend my client

18:55.768 --> 18:57.902
Against these
lurid accusations.

18:57.971 --> 19:01.438
I'm sorry, ms. Diggs,
but mr. Dubois is correct.

19:01.474 --> 19:03.541
<i> The diary is inadmissible.</i>

19:03.610 --> 19:05.042
<i> Court's adjourned.</i>

19:05.111 --> 19:07.378
<i> We will reconvene at 1:30.</i>

19:07.513 --> 19:12.517
[light dramatic music]

19:12.652 --> 19:14.519
Avery:
<i> Okay, you sure?</i>

19:16.489 --> 19:20.257
Yes, but is there anyone else,
any other contact person?

19:23.863 --> 19:24.996
I understand.

19:25.131 --> 19:26.563
[clears throat]

19:27.100 --> 19:28.599
No, thank you.

19:31.871 --> 19:36.941
Dr. Mcdonaugh:
<i> I treated students under the</i>
<i> authority of indian affairs.</i>

19:36.943 --> 19:38.376
<i> Administered</i>
<i> fluoride treatments,</i>

19:38.511 --> 19:40.678
Conducted general check ups,
that sort of thing.

19:40.680 --> 19:42.280
Can you speak to the general
health of the students

19:42.282 --> 19:44.348
That you observed
during your visits?

19:44.350 --> 19:47.351
Yes, uh, I frequently
encountered children

19:47.420 --> 19:49.820
Who had visible bruises,

19:49.822 --> 19:52.623
<i> Lesions, cracked teeth.</i>

19:52.659 --> 19:55.592
Did they ever explain how
they acquired their injuries?

19:55.594 --> 19:58.429
Dr. Mcdonaugh:
<i> I started stopping some</i>
<i> of them in the hallways</i>

19:58.498 --> 20:00.031
<i> And outside just to chat,</i>
<i> you know,</i>

20:00.033 --> 20:02.333
When sister mary grace
wasn't around.

20:03.670 --> 20:05.836
<i> That's when some of them</i>
<i> were brave enough to tell me</i>

20:05.872 --> 20:08.505
That sister mary grace
goaded them into fighting.

20:08.641 --> 20:10.374
Objection. Hearsay.

20:10.410 --> 20:11.842
Judge russo:
<i> Sustained.</i>

20:15.381 --> 20:16.913
Dr. Mcdonaugh,

20:17.984 --> 20:19.783
Can you identify this child?

20:22.555 --> 20:24.021
I...

20:28.228 --> 20:29.693
That's you.

20:32.398 --> 20:33.764
Doug:
<i> Thank you, your honour.</i>

20:33.800 --> 20:35.766
I have no further
questions for the witness.

20:37.604 --> 20:38.902
Dubois:
<i> Dr. Mcdonaugh.</i>

20:38.938 --> 20:40.404
[clears throat]

20:41.941 --> 20:43.807
How may years did
you treat children

20:43.843 --> 20:45.343
At the pine river day school?

20:45.478 --> 20:47.278
Uh, for 43 years.

20:47.280 --> 20:49.880
And yet during
all those years,

20:49.949 --> 20:52.683
Despite your alleged
concern for these children,

20:52.818 --> 20:54.618
You never spoke to
anyone about it?

20:54.620 --> 20:58.555
I reported my observations to
my supervisor at the time-

20:58.557 --> 21:00.725
But you never made an
official complaint.

21:01.827 --> 21:04.762
[light dramatic music]

21:04.764 --> 21:06.229
No.

21:07.033 --> 21:08.432
I see.

21:09.235 --> 21:11.168
Dubois:
<i> Dr. Mcdonaugh,</i>

21:11.304 --> 21:13.337
If the children under
your medical care

21:13.472 --> 21:16.306
<i> Were really suffering,</i>

21:16.342 --> 21:18.609
Why didn't you
try to help them?

21:18.611 --> 21:20.511
<i> Why didn't you do anything?</i>

21:20.580 --> 21:23.180
Why aren't you
sitting right there

21:23.182 --> 21:25.783
<i> Next to my client</i>
<i> facing charges?</i>

21:25.852 --> 21:27.451
You're right.

21:28.988 --> 21:30.721
I should've done something.
I...

21:33.592 --> 21:35.125
I am responsible.

21:38.665 --> 21:40.263
I'm so sorry.

21:41.067 --> 21:43.534
<i> I should've tried harder.</i>

21:43.536 --> 21:46.503
[sombre music]

21:53.346 --> 21:54.745
Andrea:
<i> Hey.</i>

21:54.747 --> 21:58.215
Relax, it's not like I'm
gonna throw you overboard.

21:58.284 --> 21:59.850
How can you even
joke about that?

21:59.985 --> 22:01.118
Aw shit.

22:01.187 --> 22:02.787
Sorry.

22:02.789 --> 22:03.920
<i> You're right.</i>

22:03.956 --> 22:06.156
<i> But hey, you said some</i>
<i> pretty crazy stuff,</i>

22:06.225 --> 22:08.959
Like accusing my brother
of getting people killed.

22:09.095 --> 22:11.027
Yeah, your brother's a
liar and I have proof.

22:11.064 --> 22:12.163
What kind of proof?

22:12.165 --> 22:13.430
<i> I saw the pathology report.</i>

22:13.566 --> 22:15.733
Contradicts everything brian
said about what happened

22:15.735 --> 22:16.767
To your worker on that boat.

22:16.902 --> 22:18.402
Not my worker.

22:18.471 --> 22:20.738
I don't work for the
family business.

22:20.807 --> 22:22.272
By choice.

22:24.110 --> 22:25.776
Still a clawford.

22:25.911 --> 22:27.644
Don't do that.

22:27.680 --> 22:30.781
Don't make assumptions about
me based on my last name.

22:34.987 --> 22:36.353
What are you
doing right now?

22:36.389 --> 22:37.621
Let's go for dinner.

22:37.623 --> 22:38.989
Why would I do that?

22:39.125 --> 22:41.959
So you can see how fun
and not evil I am.

22:42.094 --> 22:43.794
I'm pursuing a case
against your family.

22:43.929 --> 22:46.597
No shop talk. Promise.

22:46.599 --> 22:49.733
In fact, I never talk shop due
to my strict personal code.

22:49.736 --> 22:50.801
Which is?

22:50.936 --> 22:52.336
Not to be boring.

22:52.405 --> 22:54.338
So. Dinner?

22:56.509 --> 22:58.108
<i> You coming?</i>

22:59.612 --> 23:01.678
Doug:
<i> How long were you a student</i>
<i> at pine river day school?</i>

23:01.714 --> 23:09.353
[tense music]

23:09.355 --> 23:11.555
Well, they were, um,

23:11.557 --> 23:13.824
They were kinda run like,
uh, elementary schools.

23:13.959 --> 23:18.696
So from primary
to grade six.

23:18.698 --> 23:20.364
Were you ever
physically struck?

23:21.934 --> 23:23.634
Yes.

23:23.703 --> 23:25.436
Doug:
<i> Were you ever sexually</i>
<i> assaulted at school?</i>

23:25.571 --> 23:26.503
Preposterous!

23:26.539 --> 23:27.538
Mr. Dubois.

23:27.540 --> 23:28.539
Yeah, I'm sorry.

23:28.674 --> 23:30.608
Judge russo:
<i> No more outbursts.</i>

23:30.610 --> 23:34.845
[tense music]

23:34.980 --> 23:36.046
No.

23:36.182 --> 23:37.747
When did the hitting start?

23:38.918 --> 23:42.920
[tense music]

23:42.989 --> 23:44.522
It was, um...

23:45.358 --> 23:52.296
[tense music]

23:52.298 --> 23:53.931
♪

23:53.933 --> 23:56.133
[donald sighs]

23:56.268 --> 23:59.269
[muffled whispering]

24:00.139 --> 24:01.805
Donald?

24:01.874 --> 24:04.407
[tense music]

24:04.444 --> 24:05.876
Doug:
<i> Your honour, these are</i>
<i> highly emotional proceedings</i>

24:05.945 --> 24:07.144
<i> For my client.</i>

24:07.146 --> 24:09.146
I'd like to request a
recess until tomorrow.

24:09.281 --> 24:10.214
Judge russo:
<i> Granted.</i>

24:10.349 --> 24:11.548
<i> Yes.</i>

24:11.584 --> 24:13.517
<i> Court's adjourned</i>
<i> until tomorrow.</i>

24:15.188 --> 24:16.187
Doug:
<i> It's okay.</i>

24:16.322 --> 24:17.822
<i> Take your time.</i>

24:41.047 --> 24:43.647
Are you from the
insurance company?

24:43.782 --> 24:46.816
No, um, I'm actually
here for something else.

24:48.821 --> 24:50.354
You're avery mueller.

24:52.558 --> 24:54.258
I guess you should come in.

24:56.662 --> 24:59.062
<i> She filled out that</i>
<i> form before she died.</i>

24:59.064 --> 25:00.898
She didn't wanna be
contacted by you.

25:01.033 --> 25:02.766
But she didn't mail it in.

25:02.902 --> 25:05.436
She was really sick
the last few months.

25:05.438 --> 25:07.237
Not like it matters
now though.

25:08.674 --> 25:10.074
[avery sighs]

25:10.843 --> 25:12.276
So you're my half sister.

25:13.279 --> 25:14.811
Technically, I guess so.

25:16.081 --> 25:17.614
Avery:
<i> And you really didn't</i>
<i> know about me?</i>

25:17.650 --> 25:19.215
Kelly:
<i> She never mentioned you.</i>

25:21.353 --> 25:22.819
I was pretty shocked.

25:23.990 --> 25:27.524
Did she say anything about
who my birth father was?

25:27.593 --> 25:30.094
That's not something she
would talk about with me.

25:32.364 --> 25:34.531
It's one of the things
I wanted to ask her.

25:36.302 --> 25:37.867
<i> You have a photo of her?</i>

25:46.445 --> 25:51.615
[melancholy music]

25:51.651 --> 25:55.185
Avery:
<i> It's kinda hard to see</i>
<i> what she really looks like.</i>

25:55.221 --> 25:58.022
Sorry but I have a
lot to deal with here.

25:58.024 --> 25:59.590
<i> I'm waiting for someone from</i>
<i> the insurance company and-</i>

25:59.659 --> 26:02.192
Of course.
Of course.

26:02.194 --> 26:03.660
Uh...

26:08.267 --> 26:10.467
I'm sorry for your loss.

26:10.536 --> 26:16.073
[light dramatic music]

26:16.075 --> 26:19.876
Andrea:
<i> I lived in toronto for a</i>
<i> while and then vancouver.</i>

26:19.912 --> 26:21.878
The condo market is insane

26:21.914 --> 26:24.648
But we are not gonna
talk about that.

26:24.717 --> 26:26.182
Why not?

26:26.953 --> 26:28.352
Because it's really boring.

26:29.422 --> 26:31.688
So, why do you do it?

26:31.824 --> 26:33.557
I make good money.

26:33.626 --> 26:35.159
I make people happy.

26:38.497 --> 26:39.796
Truth?

26:39.832 --> 26:41.231
Of course.

26:41.367 --> 26:43.967
I don't like confrontation.

26:43.970 --> 26:46.637
Like, I could never
do what brian does.

26:46.639 --> 26:49.139
Be a corrupt,
ruthless businessman?

26:51.577 --> 26:53.510
Brian's a nice guy.

26:53.512 --> 26:55.646
<i> You just don't know him.</i>

26:55.781 --> 26:56.780
Right, sure.

26:56.782 --> 26:58.915
Why do you do what you do?

26:58.951 --> 27:01.318
Oh, I think I'm still
trying to figure that out.

27:02.588 --> 27:04.521
But I'm actually really
excited about this case

27:04.590 --> 27:06.156
I'm currently working on.

27:08.260 --> 27:09.827
But we agreed not
to talk about work.

27:09.962 --> 27:13.197
So let's get more wine.

27:18.337 --> 27:20.938
Ooh, smells good.

27:20.940 --> 27:23.941
Bit overdone, what,
45 minutes late.

27:23.943 --> 27:25.476
[phone dings]

27:25.611 --> 27:29.079
I'm sorry, this case is
just really tough right now,

27:29.115 --> 27:34.084
<i> And it looks like it might've</i>
<i> just completely fallen apart.</i>

27:34.153 --> 27:35.753
<i> I'm gonna tell</i>
<i> those guys I...</i>

27:35.888 --> 27:39.156
[pots clattering]

27:39.158 --> 27:40.590
Marcie:
<i> Okay.</i>

27:41.360 --> 27:42.593
I'm turning off my phone.

27:48.434 --> 27:49.900
Let's talk.

27:51.103 --> 27:53.903
<i> I know you're going</i>
<i> through a lot right now</i>

27:53.939 --> 27:56.906
<i> Around all this stuff with</i>
<i> your adoption records.</i>

27:56.942 --> 27:58.541
It's about you, marcie.

27:59.778 --> 28:01.245
Right?

28:01.380 --> 28:03.814
It's always about you,
isn't it?

28:03.816 --> 28:05.782
Wait, what are you
talking about right now?

28:07.720 --> 28:10.120
Marcie, I'm-I'm there for
you every step of the way.

28:13.159 --> 28:15.059
I even risked my
own career for you.

28:16.295 --> 28:18.062
Hell, you didn't even
have enough grace

28:18.197 --> 28:19.530
To offer me a job.

28:19.665 --> 28:21.899
So you...You wanna
work for me?

28:22.034 --> 28:23.567
Is that where this is coming
from because I don't know--

28:23.636 --> 28:25.168
Oh my gosh.

28:26.405 --> 28:31.007
Marcie, you tell me that
rolanda was already suicidal

28:31.043 --> 28:33.744
Before she walked into
m&m like it was nothing!

28:33.813 --> 28:35.812
Okay, avery,
please don't go there.

28:35.881 --> 28:37.080
How you gonna tell me
not to go there, marcie?

28:37.116 --> 28:38.015
Marcie:
<i> Please don't go there.</i>

28:38.150 --> 28:39.683
It wasn't nothing to me!

28:41.887 --> 28:43.987
Marcie, you didn't for once
think about how that information

28:43.989 --> 28:45.522
Affected me!

28:46.291 --> 28:47.624
Much less even apologize!

28:47.693 --> 28:48.658
Apologize?

28:48.694 --> 28:50.960
<i> Yes, apologize!</i>
-Wow, oh my gosh!

28:50.996 --> 28:52.028
Really?

28:52.064 --> 28:53.863
Marcie, everybody blamed me.

28:54.967 --> 28:56.166
You blamed me,

28:56.202 --> 28:58.068
Your father blamed me.

28:58.203 --> 29:01.238
<i> It changed my life.</i>

29:01.240 --> 29:03.506
And you wanna walk in here
like "I'm unburdened now,

29:03.542 --> 29:05.108
"I'm better now?"

29:06.312 --> 29:08.312
So what about me, marcie?

29:09.815 --> 29:12.215
Marcie:
<i> You're-you're-you're</i>
<i> kidding me right now, right?</i>

29:13.886 --> 29:15.418
Marcie, I'm sick of this.

29:19.458 --> 29:21.424
You never fought for this.

29:22.795 --> 29:24.260
<i> I'm always the one chasing,</i>

29:24.296 --> 29:26.496
<i> And what the hell</i>
<i> was I even thinking?</i>

29:28.067 --> 29:30.667
Marcie, everything
is about you.

29:30.703 --> 29:33.203
And I'm choking on
your narcissism.

29:37.743 --> 29:39.242
Get out.

29:39.978 --> 29:41.879
[light dramatic music]

29:42.014 --> 29:43.647
Enjoy the food.

29:43.782 --> 29:50.687
[light dramatic music]

29:50.756 --> 29:52.990
♪

29:52.992 --> 29:54.457
Constructions.

29:55.127 --> 29:56.293
Thank you.

29:56.295 --> 29:57.627
Oh, I'm getting this.

29:57.696 --> 29:59.729
No way.
-<i> I invited you.</i>

29:59.799 --> 30:02.265
Also, I make more money.

30:02.334 --> 30:03.333
Excuse me?

30:03.335 --> 30:04.734
Andrea:
<i> My parents are rich.</i>

30:04.736 --> 30:06.236
Your parents are cops.

30:07.373 --> 30:08.438
I googled you.

30:08.507 --> 30:10.240
That is so crass.

30:10.276 --> 30:11.675
You think just 'cause
you have money means-

30:11.810 --> 30:14.044
Please. Let me.

30:14.947 --> 30:16.512
You can get it next time.

30:18.050 --> 30:19.649
Next time.

30:19.685 --> 30:21.484
That's subtle.

30:21.554 --> 30:24.555
I think we both know
I'm not the subtle type.

30:24.690 --> 30:32.729
[upbeat music]

30:32.731 --> 30:35.965
Hey, can I get a
vodka tonic, please?

30:36.869 --> 30:43.806
[upbeat music]

30:43.843 --> 30:53.483
♪

30:53.552 --> 30:54.885
Hey, what are you-

30:55.020 --> 30:56.552
What are you doing here?

30:59.158 --> 31:00.690
Hot date.

31:01.360 --> 31:02.692
You?

31:02.728 --> 31:06.529
Just, um, needed
to take a breath.

31:07.433 --> 31:08.832
[iris sighs]

31:10.035 --> 31:18.508
[upbeat music continues]

31:18.644 --> 31:20.076
Disappointed?

31:21.313 --> 31:24.113
Me? The woman who sobbed her
way through a first date?

31:24.149 --> 31:25.315
No.

31:25.450 --> 31:27.016
No, I'm not disappointed.

31:29.054 --> 31:31.755
You're gonna be fine, okay?

31:31.824 --> 31:33.523
Everything'll be fine.

31:33.659 --> 31:35.091
I know.

31:36.128 --> 31:37.460
[iris sighs]

31:37.496 --> 31:44.467
[upbeat music continues]

31:44.503 --> 31:52.508
♪

31:52.544 --> 31:55.846
<i> ♪ 'cause you know</i>
<i> we're a lost cause</i>

31:55.981 --> 31:58.915
<i> ♪ oh oh oh ♪</i>

32:05.223 --> 32:08.091
[birds chirping]

32:14.633 --> 32:16.900
Andrea:
<i> Oh my god look at you.</i>

32:16.902 --> 32:18.368
I didn't kidnap you.

32:18.437 --> 32:20.437
You came here on your
own accord, remember?

32:20.439 --> 32:23.106
Ah, you're the one who ordered
the second bottle of wine.

32:23.108 --> 32:26.710
Yeah, and then I had to
finish the whole thing myself

32:26.779 --> 32:28.578
'cause you were so uptight.

32:28.580 --> 32:29.645
I am not uptight.

32:29.682 --> 32:31.280
Prove it.

32:33.385 --> 32:39.656
[light music]

32:39.658 --> 32:41.591
Iris:
<i> There was never enough money.</i>

32:45.631 --> 32:48.465
We went to parlee beach every
summer but that's about it.

32:52.938 --> 32:55.004
Avery:
<i> So these are postcards</i>
<i> of all the places</i>

32:55.040 --> 32:56.540
<i> You wanna travel to.</i>

32:57.342 --> 33:04.814
[light music continues]

33:04.850 --> 33:06.282
Escapes.

33:09.288 --> 33:10.687
Iris...

33:14.593 --> 33:17.761
[avery sighs]

33:17.830 --> 33:19.229
<i> ♪ even if you can't see me</i>

33:19.298 --> 33:24.901
<i> ♪ no, I can't keep up</i>
<i> with these games you play</i>

33:24.937 --> 33:27.104
<i> ♪ some day</i>

33:27.239 --> 33:31.575
<i> ♪ I'm falling into</i>
<i> you transcend</i>

33:31.710 --> 33:37.680
<i> ♪ you won't let me go, no ♪</i>

33:37.750 --> 33:38.982
Hey.

33:38.984 --> 33:40.917
<i> Listen, I'm really</i>
<i> worried about donald.</i>

33:40.986 --> 33:41.885
Marcie:
<i> Why?</i>

33:42.020 --> 33:42.819
What's up?

33:42.954 --> 33:44.588
He never returned
my calls last night

33:44.723 --> 33:46.055
And his wife said he
left early this morning,

33:46.091 --> 33:47.924
But he's not answering her
phone calls now either.

33:47.926 --> 33:51.294
Well if anyone understands
how he's feeling, it's you.

33:51.296 --> 33:53.029
And that's why I'm worried.

33:53.164 --> 33:55.999
[tense music]

33:56.134 --> 33:57.634
Where would you go?

33:59.104 --> 34:00.570
[doug sighs]

34:01.506 --> 34:07.276
[haunting music]
[birds chirping]

34:10.449 --> 34:12.482
Doug:
<i> Hey, you had me worried.</i>

34:12.484 --> 34:14.350
<i> I had to take a few</i>
<i> spins around pine river</i>

34:14.386 --> 34:16.419
<i> Before I spotted your car.</i>

34:16.422 --> 34:19.289
I had to come back here
to remind myself that

34:19.358 --> 34:20.891
I'm not a child anymore.

34:21.026 --> 34:22.159
<i> I don't know where you</i>
<i> get your strength from,</i>

34:22.294 --> 34:25.495
But it's admirable.

34:25.497 --> 34:26.696
<i> That's for sure.</i>

34:26.765 --> 34:28.364
My mother.

34:29.568 --> 34:31.734
You know she went to
residential school, eh.

34:33.372 --> 34:34.704
<i> She used to tell me stories</i>

34:34.773 --> 34:37.240
<i> About how she worked</i>
<i> in the orchard,</i>

34:37.375 --> 34:40.143
But she wasn't allowed
to eat the apples.

34:42.214 --> 34:44.447
Yeah, there were severe
consequences for anyone

34:44.516 --> 34:46.115
Caught stealing food.

34:50.188 --> 34:54.057
When I started school here she
couldn't come to the orchard

34:54.192 --> 34:57.860
<i> Because it brought back</i>
<i> too many bad memories.</i>

35:00.599 --> 35:03.533
<i> So I started picking apples</i>
<i> and bringing them home to her.</i>

35:06.605 --> 35:08.338
Eventually she dealt with it.

35:09.541 --> 35:11.507
She learned how to
bake apple pie.

35:12.711 --> 35:14.878
<i> My mother survived so</i>
<i> much more than I did.</i>

35:16.982 --> 35:18.781
She never had her
day in court.

35:21.753 --> 35:24.320
I had my chance,

35:24.389 --> 35:25.455
<i> And I couldn't stop</i>
<i> thinking about</i>

35:25.590 --> 35:28.158
How it shoulda been
her on the stand.

35:28.293 --> 35:29.959
Doug:
<i> Healing is messy.</i>

35:29.995 --> 35:31.928
<i> Just because you're not as</i>
<i> traumatized as someone else</i>

35:31.930 --> 35:34.164
Doesn't mean your
story's irrelevant.

35:34.299 --> 35:35.298
Doesn't mean that
sister mary grace

35:35.433 --> 35:37.433
Should get away
with what she did.

35:37.469 --> 35:38.568
<i> You know, everyone</i>
<i> in that courtroom</i>

35:38.604 --> 35:43.339
Looks at her and sees
this harmless old lady.

35:43.375 --> 35:45.175
<i> But when she looked at</i>
<i> me in that courtroom</i>

35:45.244 --> 35:48.110
And I heard her voice,

35:50.883 --> 35:53.650
I was afraid all over again,
just like in school.

35:55.987 --> 35:57.420
I froze.

35:58.456 --> 36:00.723
<i> Donald, your mother</i>
<i> is proud of you.</i>

36:00.792 --> 36:03.126
She's watching over you and
she's right there with you

36:03.261 --> 36:04.728
<i> When you're on the stand.</i>

36:05.931 --> 36:07.063
<i> Not everyone who looks</i>
<i> at sister mary grace</i>

36:07.099 --> 36:08.898
Sees a harmless
little old lady.

36:10.636 --> 36:12.202
I see something,

36:13.238 --> 36:15.204
Something she tries to hide.

36:16.675 --> 36:18.241
You see it?

36:20.012 --> 36:22.746
And I think I know how we can
make everyone else see it too.

36:24.283 --> 36:26.016
[donald sighs]
[sombre music]

36:28.287 --> 36:29.886
Marcie:
<i> Hey, coll, wait up.</i>

36:30.021 --> 36:31.554
Colleen:
<i> Marcie, hi.</i>

36:31.557 --> 36:33.155
You got my message?

36:33.759 --> 36:35.024
Who contacted you?

36:35.060 --> 36:36.226
Collins.

36:36.295 --> 36:37.761
Officious little prick.

36:37.896 --> 36:39.563
I told him you were
one of my star lawyers

36:39.698 --> 36:41.231
And sent him packing.

36:42.301 --> 36:43.900
Well I would've loved
to have seen that.

36:44.035 --> 36:45.235
Thanks.

36:45.237 --> 36:46.303
The barristers' society,

36:46.305 --> 36:48.171
They have to justify
their existence, right?

36:48.306 --> 36:50.440
So they're going after
specious complaints

36:50.442 --> 36:51.308
And slapping a few wrists.

36:51.443 --> 36:52.441
Let them.

36:52.477 --> 36:54.310
So, this has happened
to you before?

36:55.180 --> 36:56.713
No.

36:56.782 --> 36:59.049
You're friends with
judge dewey, right?

36:59.051 --> 37:01.751
Why would she even file a
complaint in the first place?

37:01.820 --> 37:03.386
Was friends with her.

37:03.889 --> 37:04.587
Who knows?

37:04.656 --> 37:06.189
She's a terrible person.

37:06.324 --> 37:07.524
<i> You're gonna be fine.</i>

37:07.659 --> 37:09.325
You've got a lot of good
people in your corner.

37:09.361 --> 37:10.826
Like me.

37:11.563 --> 37:14.864
It's just weird, you know?

37:14.866 --> 37:16.866
<i> Weird for her to wait</i>
<i> so long to do it.</i>

37:17.002 --> 37:19.602
Like, if she's so upset
with my behaviour,

37:19.671 --> 37:21.671
Why wouldn't she
file at that time?

37:21.707 --> 37:23.473
It's a good question.
I wonder...

37:25.043 --> 37:26.176
[light dramatic music]

37:26.178 --> 37:27.743
What?

37:27.779 --> 37:29.079
[colleen scoffs]

37:29.214 --> 37:30.080
Never mind.

37:30.215 --> 37:32.182
Call me if you
need anything.

37:32.184 --> 37:35.885
[light dramatic music]

37:35.954 --> 37:37.420
Ellery:
<i> Mom, I was right!</i>

37:37.555 --> 37:39.288
The pathology
report proves it.

37:39.290 --> 37:41.124
Basil allen didn't get
drunk and fall overboard.

37:41.126 --> 37:43.226
There's every indication
that he was assaulted.

37:43.295 --> 37:45.094
Chozanne:
<i> I know, I know.</i>

37:45.130 --> 37:46.262
I just got a call.

37:46.331 --> 37:48.764
<i> The rcmp now say that</i>
<i> basil allen was attacked</i>

37:48.800 --> 37:50.633
And thrown overboard
during a fight.

37:50.669 --> 37:52.435
Wait, so they did keep
the investigation open?

37:52.504 --> 37:54.070
Someone came forward.

37:54.205 --> 37:55.271
Um, I don't understand.

37:55.307 --> 37:56.472
Who?

37:56.474 --> 37:58.107
<i> I asked for a copy of</i>
<i> the arrest report,</i>

37:58.176 --> 38:00.777
<i> Which don't worry,</i>
<i> I'll forward to you.</i>

38:00.912 --> 38:05.014
<i>A temp worker named mike mccleod</i>
<i> was also on the boat.</i>

38:05.050 --> 38:08.584
<i> He turned himself in and</i>
<i> made a full confession.</i>

38:08.586 --> 38:13.290
[tense music]

38:13.425 --> 38:14.990
Secretary:
<i> Right in the middle of...</i>

38:16.361 --> 38:19.061
Colleen, what can
I do for you?

38:19.097 --> 38:20.663
You can lay off my people.

38:21.600 --> 38:22.598
What are you talking about?

38:22.634 --> 38:24.601
Your specious,
underhanded complaint

38:24.603 --> 38:26.402
To the crown and
barristers' society.

38:26.538 --> 38:29.539
Judge dewey:
<i> "specious" and "underhanded".</i>

38:30.609 --> 38:32.174
Like when a friend
goes behind your back

38:32.210 --> 38:34.544
To undermine you and try
to derail your career?

38:34.613 --> 38:37.013
You wanna come for someone,
come for me.

38:37.082 --> 38:39.082
Don't go after my innocent
friends and colleagues.

38:39.151 --> 38:41.684
[tense music]

38:41.753 --> 38:43.286
Are they innocent?

38:43.288 --> 38:46.522
Hm, I guess that
remains to be seen.

38:48.159 --> 38:50.159
I'm ashamed I ever
called you a friend.

38:52.964 --> 38:54.898
[speaking in mi'kmaq]
my name is kitpu.

38:54.900 --> 38:56.966
It's the mi'kmaq
word for eagle,

38:57.035 --> 38:59.168
But my english name
is donald christmas.

38:59.204 --> 39:01.571
L'nuisin?

39:01.573 --> 39:03.773
I asked him if he
spoke the language.

39:03.775 --> 39:05.708
Kishka'h ji.

39:05.777 --> 39:06.976
Just a little bit.

39:07.012 --> 39:08.845
<i> But I'm not fluent because</i>

39:08.914 --> 39:11.447
<i> I wasn't allowed to speak</i>
<i> my language growing up.</i>

39:11.583 --> 39:14.250
Doug:
<i> Yesterday you confirmed that</i>
<i> you were physically struck</i>

39:14.252 --> 39:15.719
As a student at pine river.

39:15.854 --> 39:17.386
Mmhmm.

39:17.388 --> 39:18.988
Doug:
<i> Kitpu, can you identify the</i>
<i> person that assaulted you?</i>

39:19.124 --> 39:20.656
This is ridiculous.
Stop this.

39:20.658 --> 39:21.758
Just hold on, be calm.

39:21.760 --> 39:24.594
[speaking in mi'kmaq]

39:24.663 --> 39:26.029
<i> Sister mary grace.</i>

39:26.031 --> 39:28.064
[light dramatic music]

39:28.133 --> 39:31.434
Donald deserved every
beating he ever got.

39:31.436 --> 39:35.371
<i> He never listened and clearly</i>
<i> he never learned his lesson!</i>

39:35.374 --> 39:36.939
Dubois:
<i> Sister, you need</i>
<i> to calm down.</i>

39:37.008 --> 39:38.541
Calm down?

39:38.543 --> 39:40.876
Sister mary grace:
<i> He is speaking that</i>
<i> primitive language</i>

39:40.912 --> 39:42.811
That none of us can
even understand

39:42.813 --> 39:44.881
<i> Just to make up</i>
<i> lies about me!</i>

39:44.883 --> 39:45.882
[gavel thuds]

39:45.884 --> 39:47.316
Enough!

39:48.153 --> 39:50.019
<i> Court is adjourned.</i>

39:50.021 --> 39:52.655
[dramatic music]

39:55.093 --> 39:56.426
Probably the best
thing we can do, so...

39:56.561 --> 39:57.894
[sister mary grace sighs]

39:59.164 --> 40:01.430
My client has been diagnosed
with pancreatic cancer

40:01.432 --> 40:02.832
<i> And has very</i>
<i> limited time left.</i>

40:02.967 --> 40:04.567
Doug:
<i> Wow, how convenient.</i>

40:04.702 --> 40:07.437
Yes, it's because
I work for god

40:07.572 --> 40:09.038
And god takes care of me.

40:09.107 --> 40:10.840
We can provide the
medical records

40:10.975 --> 40:13.275
Attesting to the
recent diagnosis.

40:13.311 --> 40:14.710
Is that what you want?

40:14.746 --> 40:16.279
To send a dying
woman to prison?

40:17.382 --> 40:18.782
Yeah.

40:19.885 --> 40:21.116
We'd like to offer
a plea deal.

40:21.153 --> 40:22.051
An apology.

40:22.187 --> 40:24.353
I will never apologize!

40:24.423 --> 40:26.756
<i> My actions were</i>
<i> sanctioned by the church.</i>

40:26.758 --> 40:29.659
I would never accept
an apology from you

40:29.728 --> 40:31.227
Because it would
mean nothing.

40:31.296 --> 40:32.362
<i> You know, the word sorry</i>

40:32.497 --> 40:34.530
<i> Doesn't have a meaning</i>
<i> in my culture.</i>

40:34.599 --> 40:38.301
<i> The only way to fix a problem</i>
<i> is by changed behaviour.</i>

40:38.370 --> 40:39.535
Doug:
<i> This is insulting.</i>

40:39.571 --> 40:41.003
She couldn't control
herself in the courtroom

40:41.072 --> 40:42.405
Or in this very moment.

40:42.407 --> 40:44.874
<i> Could you imagine what</i>
<i> she did to her students?</i>

40:44.876 --> 40:45.942
An apology is unacceptable.

40:45.944 --> 40:46.843
Sister mary grace:
<i> I answer to god.</i>

40:46.978 --> 40:48.144
I do not answer to you.

40:48.279 --> 40:50.379
Please, stop.

40:50.449 --> 40:52.781
Marcie:
<i> This deal's gonna</i>
<i> work on our terms:</i>

40:52.818 --> 40:55.551
Sister mary grace will
make a kgb statement

40:55.620 --> 40:57.353
<i> Providing the names of</i>
<i> her co-conspirators</i>

40:57.422 --> 40:59.489
So that when she
dies the evidence

40:59.624 --> 41:00.823
Will still be
admissible in court.

41:00.859 --> 41:03.025
Now, she can either take the
deal or she can die in prison.

41:03.061 --> 41:04.494
[dramatic music]

41:07.666 --> 41:09.298
[doug sighs]

41:09.334 --> 41:10.500
What's this?

41:10.635 --> 41:12.836
Doug:
<i> Affidavits signed by</i>
<i> sister mary grace</i>

